Package: PPDisentangle
Title: Causal Inference for Spatiotemporal Point Processes via Stochastic EM
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Duncan", "Clark", email = "duncan-clark@outlook.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Conor", "Kresin", role = "aut"),
    person("Louis", "Davis", role = "aut"),
    person("Martin", "Hazelton", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Implements a Stochastic EM algorithm for causal inference on
    spatiotemporal point process data with outcome spillover. Models observed
    data as a superposition of treatment and control point processes (Hawkes
    or ETAS), recovers latent process labels via importance-weighted proposals,
    and estimates average treatment effects accounting for spatial interference.
    The ETAS module provides Omori-Utsu temporal and magnitude-dependent
    power-law spatial kernels following Zhuang et al. (2002).
